trans-unit.source: Base class for all the chart elements.
The <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref> class represents the most basic element of the chart element hierarchy.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref> class.
Releases the resources used by the <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>.
Releases the unmanaged resources used by the <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref> and optionally releases the managed resources.
`True` to release both managed and unmanaged resources; `False` to release only unmanaged resources.
Determines whether the specified <xref href="System.Object"></xref> is equal to the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to compare with the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>.
`True` if the specified <xref href="System.Object"></xref> is equal to the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement"></xref>; otherwise, `False`.
Returns a hash function for a particular type.
An `integer` value that represents the hash code for the current <xref href="System.Object"></xref>.
Gets or sets an object associated with this chart element.
The <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.ChartElement.Tag%2A> property can be used to store additional data with this chart element.
An <xref href="System.Object"></xref> associated with this chart element.
Returns a string that represents the current <xref href="System.Object"></xref>.
A `string` value that represents the current <xref href="System.Object"></xref>.
